üõ†Ô∏è FIX 1: SEVERITY COUNTER LOGIC

Please update the logic that controls the severity counters (High / Medium / Low) on the report canvas sidebar.

Requirements:
- When the "Current Page Only" toggle is enabled, the severity counters should reflect ONLY the visible and actively selected violation boxes.
- If all boxes are in the unselected (default) state, all three counters should show zero.
- The counters should update dynamically:
   - When a box is selected or unselected
   - When a filter is applied
   - When navigating between report pages

Confirm that the counters are correctly zeroed out when no boxes are selected and increment only based on what is actively checked.

üõ†Ô∏è FIX 2: FCRA REVIEW SUMMARY SPACING

Please tighten the vertical spacing between violation descriptions in the FCRA Review Summary panel.

- Set vertical gap between items (e.g., `.fcra-review-item` or `.review-entry`) to 6‚Äì8px
- Ensure there is no excess padding or line-height that adds visual noise
- Maintain good mobile responsiveness:
   - On screens narrower than 768px, allow slightly larger line-height but still limit margin-bottom to 10px max

Suggested CSS:
.fcra-review-item {
  margin-bottom: 8px;
  line-height: 1.35;
}
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .fcra-review-item {
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    line-height: 1.45;
  }
}

üí° Optional: Add a utility class or scoped override if the gap is being inherited globally from another CSS rule.

Please confirm when both issues are resolved and tested.

üõ†Ô∏è UI ALIGNMENT FIX ‚Äî Top-Level Layout for FCRA Review Summary & Report Canvas

üéØ Objective: Restore proper vertical alignment across the main layout row ‚Äî specifically:

FCRA Review Summary (sidebar panel)

Report Canvas (main content viewer)

All must align visually and structurally with the top edge of the View Toggle bar (viotagger | report | evidence)

üîç CURRENT ISSUE
Both the .frca-summary-panel (right sidebar) and .report-canvas-container (main content column) are visually shifted down

This misalignment breaks the intended grid lock-in across the top bar

The view toggle bar sits higher than the elements to its right and left ‚Äî this was not the case in the prior design

‚úÖ ALIGNMENT FIX INSTRUCTIONS
1. Establish Unified Vertical Alignment
Wrap the View Toggle, Canvas, and FCRA Sidebar in a shared horizontal flex container or grid row

Use align-items: flex-start to force top alignment of all three children

2. Eliminate Unnecessary Margins/Padding
Inspect and remove any rogue margin-top or padding-top values on:

.frca-summary-panel

.report-canvas-container

Any nested wrappers inside those components

üìê RESPONSIVE REQUIREMENTS
The fix must work seamlessly across all breakpoints:

css
Copy
Edit
@media (min-width: 1024px) {
  .main-layout-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 24px;
  }

  .frca-summary-panel,
  .report-canvas-container {
    margin-top: 0;
    padding-top: 0;
  }
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .main-layout-row {
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 16px;
  }
}
‚úÖ SUCCESS CRITERIA
 FCRA Review Summary, Report Canvas, and View Toggle are visually and structurally top-aligned

 No margin/padding pushes any layout element down

